dataStructure.name: sid.org.tmforum.tip.resource.res.log.soft.SoftwareCommand
dataStructure.description:
SoftwareCommands describe the sets of features that are programmable by a particular PartyRole (e.g., a Developer, or NetworkOperator, and in rare cases, an EndUser). This should not be confused with Capabilities. Capabilities define what features and functions are available at a given moment for the Resource. Thus, SoftwareCommands represent the specific commands that are available in a device, whereas Capabilities represent higher-level generic functions available in a Resource. For exampe, the ability to perform BGP routing is a Capability, whereas the actual commands used to implement BGP routing are SoftwareCommands.

This entity is optional
dataStructure.label: SoftwareCommand
